A group, South East Peace Agitators, has commended the “efforts and sacrifices made by the G-23 group during the last general election and said that President Muhammadu Buhari’s increased votes in the South-east in the last election was as a result of efforts put up by the group. Disclosing this in a statement, the National Chairman of the group, Chike Nwankwo, commended the effort of the Convener of G-23 for President Buhari, and the State Coordinator, GOGAN Anambra,  Chief Johnbosco Onunkwo, alongside others in “re-branding the President”. “President Buhari started hundreds of projects in his first tenure and completed a lot of them. The South-east did not understand that President Buhari meant well for our region till Chief Johnbosco Onunkwo started various media campaigns, rallies and conferences to educate and enlighten Igbos on various projects President Buhari embarked on to favour our region. The president’s projects and policies were projected in the region by Chief Johnbosco Onunkwo,” Nwankwo said. We’ll fulfill our promises on infrastructure for South-East, Buhari tells Ndigbo 2019: Buhari to secure landslide victory in South-East, says Sen. Uzodinma Buhari: I''ll fulfill campaign promises to Igbo Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin